[REASON:planning] <physical_use>
[REASON:planning]   <orientation>The part is mounted vertically to a wall or monitor stand via the VESA plate. The tray extends forward and angles downward at 30 degrees. The lowest point is the tray front edge at Z=10mm.</orientation>
[REASON:planning]   <contact_surfaces>The VESA plate back face (Y=0) contacts the mounting surface. The tray top surface (tilted) contacts the laptop bottom. The support struts contact the tray underside. Footprint on mount is 150x10mm.</contact_surfaces>
[REASON:planning]   <applied_forces>Laptop weight (~1.5kg) acts downward through the tray center. The 30° tilt creates a forward sliding component (~0.75kg force). The VESA plate resists the resulting torque. Struts resist bending loads from the cantilevered tray.</applied_forces>
[REASON:planning]   <containment_strategy>Gravity holds the laptop on the tilted tray. The back edge of the tray (supported by struts and fused to the VESA plate) acts as a physical stop preventing backward sliding. The shallow 30° angle minimizes forward sliding; friction and laptop bottom texture provide sufficient retention.</containment_strategy>
[REASON:planning]   <pose_intent>The laptop_tray component is tilted -30 degrees around the X axis relative to the horizontal XY plane, pivoting at the back edge (0,10,110). This matches the structured rotation tag.</pose_intent>
[REASON:planning]   <use_cycle>User screws the bracket to a VESA-compatible surface. User places laptop onto the tray. User removes laptop when finished. No moving parts or repeated insertion cycles.</use_cycle>
[REASON:planning]   <ergonomic_notes>30° tilt improves screen visibility and reduces neck strain. Front edge chamfer prevents sharp contact. Strut placement avoids blocking laptop bottom vents.</ergonomic_notes>
[REASON:planning]   <mating_object>Standard 13-15 inch laptop (approx. 300x220x20mm). VESA 100x100 mounting interface with M4 screws. Clearance holes sized 5.5mm for M4 threads.</mating_object>
[REASON:planning] </physical_use>
[REASON:planning] <feature_decisions>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="fasteners_or_mounting_holes" needed="true">VESA mounting requires four 5.5mm clearance holes in a 100x100 pattern for M4 screws to attach to monitor/wall.</decision>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="internal_cavity_or_shell" needed="false">Solid 8mm tray with explicit hex cutouts provides sufficient stiffness and material savings; shelling is unnecessary and complicates wall thickness control.</decision>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="retention_geometry" needed="false">Gravity and the solid back edge stop are sufficient for a 30° tilt; no clips or lips are needed and would interfere with laptop placement.</decision>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="load_bearing_reinforcement" needed="true">Two 15x10x40mm vertical struts are added to resist cantilever bending moments from the laptop weight.</decision>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="clearance_or_port_cutouts" needed="true">Hexagonal cutouts are explicitly requested to save material and improve airflow to the laptop bottom.</decision>
[REASON:planning]   <decision feature="moving_or_mating_interface" needed="false">The design is a rigid, fixed-angle bracket; no hinges, threads, or sliding interfaces are required.</decision>
