    * 30-degree downward-tilted laptop tray
    * Two vertical side support struts
    * Hexagonal airflow cutout pattern in tray center
    * M4 clearance mounting holes
    * 3mm fillets at strut junctions
    * 2mm chamfer on tray front edge
  assumptions:
    * Laptop thickness is ~20mm; struts are placed at X=±90mm to avoid bottom vent interference
    * VESA pattern is standard 100x100 mm MIS-D
    * PLA material with 0.2mm layer height; 30° overhang prints without supports
